    "minides": "Aston Martin's self-styled 'Super Tourer' — a 680 PS V8 grand tourer with genuine supercar pace and a completely reimagined cabin built on Aston's own E&E electrical architecture.",
    "description": "The Aston Martin DB12 launched in India on 29 September 2023 as the successor to the DB11, replacing the old V12 lineup entirely with a single Mercedes-AMG-sourced 4.0L twin-turbo V8. Billed as the world's first 'Super Tourer', it pairs genuine supercar pace (0-100 in 3.6 sec, 325 km/h top speed) with everyday GT comfort. The chassis is 7% stiffer than the DB11's, and the cabin is built on Aston's own E&E electrical architecture with a new 10.25-inch touchscreen, 12.3-inch digital cluster, and a Bowers & Wilkins 1,170W 15-speaker surround system. In October 2025, Aston revealed the range-topping DB12 S, sharing the same 4.0L V8 but uprated by 20 PS, with sportier suspension tuning and unique styling cues. India offers the DB12 in the standard Coupe and the higher-output S specification — both finished entirely through Aston Martin's 'Q' personal commissioning programme."
  },
